article.headline: UTEP 71, Hawaii 62
article.story: EL PASO, Texas (AP) -- John Tofi scored 22 points and had 10 rebounds to lead Texas-El Paso to a 71-62 victory over Hawaii as the Miners remained atop the Western Athletic Conference standings. UTEP (20-5, 11-4), which finished in last place a year ago while compiling a 6-24 record, won its ninth game in the last 10. The Miners are trailed in the WAC by Rice (10-4) and Nevada (10-5). Tofi was 9-of-11 from the field and had two assists, a block and a steal. Chris Craig and Fili Rivera each scored 14 points for UTEP. Roy Smallwood added 13 points and nine rebounds. Michael Kuebler scored all 22 of his points for Hawaii (17-8, 9-5) in the second half. Julian Sensley scored 18 points and had a team-high nine rebounds. After Hawaii fell behind 50-33 with 13:37 left in the game, Kuebler scored all 10 points in a 10-0 run that cut UTEP's lead to 50-43 with 12:05 remaining. Hawaii got no closer than seven points the rest of the way. UTEP shot 51 percent from the field while Hawaii shot just 38 percent. UTEP took control of the game midway through the first half with a 17-2 run, turning a 20-14 lead with 12:38 remaining into a 37-16 advantage with 6:14 left. Fili Rivera and John Tofi led the way during the run with seven points apiece. The Rainbow Warriors rallied with an 11-3 run to close the half and cut their halftime deficit to 40-27.
